<h2 id="exercise-4-adding-as-many-slides-as-possible">Exercise 4: Adding as many slides as possible</h2>

<p>This one combines some of the phrases from exercise #2 and #3 â€“ and does so in a way where three of the notes within the riff are â€œslidâ€ into. This creates a very distinct effect, making things sound a bit more elegant and complex (but you donâ€™t want to overdo it). Note that this comes with an extra degree of difficulty. For one, youâ€™ll need to adjust the left hand fingers-you-use slightly from the prior exercises (see my video for reference) â€“ this is so you can execute each slide while setting your fingers up to perform the slides that come afterwards. It can be tricky to learn, but at the same time very rewarding if you can master it.</p>

